Do you want to celebrate your birthday in a way that is unique to you? 

Here are a few tips to make your milestone special and celebrate fabulously!

1.Do something that feels true to you
2.If you want to create a reason to have all the people you love in one room, have a big bash with all of your friends and family 
3.If you’re more low-key, spend time with family and close friends and cater dinner in your home 
4.If the party falls on a different day, still do something special on your actual birthday - like go out to eat or see a movie
5.Have a themed party based on one of your hobbies or interests
6.Throw yourself a surprise party!

Birthday parties can be a lot of fun, but they can also be a lot of work. Consider hiring an event planner if you want to make your birthday truly one-of-a-kind. An experienced professional can assist you in developing a theme that reflects your personality and interests, and will handle all of the details so you can relax and enjoy your special day.

A true work of art, Hotel de Pourtalès was renovated and redesigned by avant-garde French designers and famous international artists to decorate the 11 accommodations spread over seven floors. 

Located on the 6th, 7th and 8th floor the Sky Penthouse is the perfect location for an intimate wedding party. This sophisticated Signature Suite offers impressive accommodations along with a dining and living room,  and a full gourmet kitchen. But what makes it especially special is the panoramic roof terrace with a private garden, and a 180 degree view of Paris, including the Eiffel Tower!
